Citations
Date: 8/9/1869
Source: Thames Journals
Author: LUSH
Vol / Page: 67
Edition: 1975
Quote: The evening was very dark and I had taken up as I left home, a `digger's lantern'; this is usually made out of a brandy [68] bottle with the bottom broken off and a candle stuck in the neck and which, held by the neck, makes a capital `rough and ready' lantern.
